  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a randomized controlled trial to investigate the optimal timing of delivery in
      clinically stable women with a suspected morbidly adherent placenta.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a randomized controlled trial to investigate the optimal timing of delivery in
      clinically stable women with a suspected morbidly adherent placenta dispositioned for a
      scheduled delivery. The primary outcome will be assessed by comparing the composite neonatal
      morbidity and composite maternal morbidity between the two groups (delivery at 34 versus 36
      weeks gestational age).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
